## Why This Is Asked
Demonstrates practical secret lifecycle management in Docker Swarm, integrating Vault for automated rotation with zero-downtime upgrades and proper secret versioning.

## Key Concepts
- Swarm secrets versioning and dynamic reattachment
- Vault-based rotation triggers and secret provisioning
- Rolling updates with start-first strategy to avoid downtime
- Health checks to confirm new secrets are loaded before removing old ones
- Atomic secret updates using add-then-remove pattern

## Code Example
```javascript
// Pseudo-automation: rotate Vault-derived Swarm secrets
async function rotateSecrets(serviceName, vaultPath) {
  // Fetch new credentials from Vault
  const newCreds = await vault.read(vaultPath);

  // Create new Swarm secrets
  const newSecrets = await createSwarmSecrets(newCreds);

  // Update service with new secrets
  await updateService(serviceName, newSecrets);

  // Verify health before cleanup
  await verifyServiceHealth(serviceName);

  // Remove old secrets
  await cleanupOldSecrets(serviceName);
}
```

## Why This Is Asked
Tests secure, rotating certs in Swarm with Vault, handling cert storage (secret vs volume), and canary semantics.

## Key Concepts
- Swarm multi-node with TLS and mTLS
- Vault PKI for dynamic certs
- Certs via writable volume + sidecar refresh
- Canary rollout with health checks and rollback
- Nginx TLS termination and service-to-service mTLS

## Code Example
```javascript
// Simple cert refresh watcher from Vault to a mounted volume
const fetch = require('node-fetch');
const fs = require('fs');
async function refresh() {
  const res = await fetch('https://vault.example/v1/pki/issue/api', { headers: { 'X-Vault-Token': process.env.VAULT_TOKEN } });
  const cert = await res.text();
  fs.writeFileSync('/certs/api.crt', cert);
}
setInterval(refresh, 5 * 60 * 1000);
```

